@rickmorris433 a wind generator attached to a vehicle adds to air resistance, effectively slowing the vehicle down, and thus needing more energy to move it. 

A car can't recharge itself while moving. He can, however, use things like regenerative brakes which converts kynetic energy back to electricity by effectively augmenting the car's resistance to movement.

The closest thing to your idea would probably be a rotor sail. Modern ships use it, but that wouldn't be practical for a car.
